AB  - The Monte Carlo method of exploring the properties of econometric estimators and significance tests has yielded a considerable amount of information that has practical value in guiding choice of technique in applied research. This paper presents a bibliography of such Monte Carlo studies over the period 1948–1972. About 150 citations are listed alphabetically by author, and also under a detailed subject-matter classification scheme.
